07:38.721 --> 07:40.580
Hoopin'.

07:40.680 --> 07:41.939
Just a couple pickup games.
No big deal.

07:42.039 --> 07:43.698
I thought you left that
street shit in Philly.

07:43.798 --> 07:45.417
Look, if you need money,
just ask.

07:45.517 --> 07:47.736
No, man, I'm done
taking handouts, all right?

07:47.836 --> 07:49.095
I need to get back
to who I used to be.

07:49.195 --> 07:50.575
Oh, what, an almost felon
with a gun charge?

07:50.675 --> 07:53.413
Listen, OK?

07:53.513 --> 07:55.052
I was being scouted
to play basketball,

07:55.152 --> 07:57.531
and when I came out here,
all of that went quiet.

07:57.631 --> 07:59.930
But I have a plan.
There's this big-time scout.

08:00.030 --> 08:02.328
His name is Doc, and he helps
a lot of kids get to D1 schools

08:02.428 --> 08:04.007
and even to the pros.

08:04.107 --> 08:06.526
OK, so what, he's like a--
like an agent?

08:06.626 --> 08:08.405
Agent-manager-coach.

08:08.505 --> 08:10.524
Look, I know it sounds sketchy,
but it's legit.

08:10.624 --> 08:12.363
OK, but he's going
to help you?

08:12.463 --> 08:14.002
No, I mean,
I got to meet him first.

08:14.102 --> 08:15.841
But look, I've been balling
with this kid named JB.

08:15.941 --> 08:17.440
He's going to make
the introduction.

08:17.540 --> 08:19.039
OK, why don't you
just let my dad help?

08:19.139 --> 08:20.838
No, bro.

08:20.938 --> 08:23.117
This is my world.
I got to do this without him.

08:23.217 --> 08:24.916
Look,
I know he's not perfect,

08:25.016 --> 08:30.233
but don't forget how
he stuck his neck out for you.

08:30.333 --> 08:33.311
Come on, Will.
We're still your family.

08:40.088 --> 08:42.746
All right, my love, help.

08:42.846 --> 08:44.625
Which one?
- Hmm.

08:44.725 --> 08:47.104
Well, the silver does
bring out your sexiness.

08:47.204 --> 08:48.663
- Mm-hmm.
- But...

08:48.763 --> 08:51.062
since you're going back
into the office,

08:51.162 --> 08:52.061
go with the brown.

08:52.161 --> 08:54.260
Mwah.

08:54.360 --> 08:55.819
Good choice.

08:55.919 --> 08:58.178
I can't believe
you're going back so soon.

08:58.278 --> 09:01.416
Well, you know, I can't
sit still for too long.

09:01.516 --> 09:03.615
Plus, your man is ready
to shake things up a little.

09:03.715 --> 09:04.894
I know you want
to change the world,

09:04.994 --> 09:06.493
but maybe ease into things
before you start

09:06.593 --> 09:08.572
getting all militant.
- I'm just following your lead.

09:08.672 --> 09:10.971
You excited for
this big interview?

09:11.071 --> 09:12.370
I mean, it's not that big.

09:12.470 --> 09:15.968
Uh, a feature article
in "Fine Art Quarterly"

09:16.068 --> 09:21.006
dedicated to the brilliant
Neeman fellow Vivian Banks?

09:21.106 --> 09:23.104
That sounds pretty big to me.

09:24.983 --> 09:26.842
I know that look.

09:26.942 --> 09:29.481
What's wrong?

09:29.581 --> 09:32.839
Well, I mean, it's hard
to celebrate anything when...

09:32.939 --> 09:34.718
Will's not home.

09:34.818 --> 09:36.637
Vy is losing faith in us.

09:36.737 --> 09:38.956
Oh, and Ashley's party.
You heard what she said.

09:39.056 --> 09:39.975
Well, I can't exactly
go grab the boy

09:39.975 --> 09:41.195
by the back of the collar

09:41.295 --> 09:42.674
and drag him through
the front door.

09:42.774 --> 09:44.353
No, but you could apologise.

09:44.453 --> 09:45.432
Apologise for what?

09:45.532 --> 09:48.231
I was right about Lou, huh?

09:48.331 --> 09:50.230
Nothing good came from Will
meeting up with him.

09:50.330 --> 09:53.308
At least he got to see
the kind of man his father is.

09:53.408 --> 09:55.707
We were wrong not to tell him.

09:55.807 --> 09:58.825
Will was doing great
until Lou walked up in here.

09:58.925 --> 10:02.863
This whole mess is his doing,
not ours.

10:04.402 --> 10:06.821
<i>♪ Uno, dos, tres, chief ♪</i>

10:06.921 --> 10:08.260
<i>♪ Every day,
I'm out to get it ♪</i>

10:08.360 --> 10:10.499
<i>♪ The hustle,
I doubt you could mimic ♪</i>

10:10.599 --> 10:12.018
<i>♪ Whole squad
about the business ♪</i>

10:12.118 --> 10:14.337
<i>♪ We can't have no doubts
